# Docs & ADR Conventions

## Docs principles
- Keep docs task-oriented (how to run, configure, deploy, troubleshoot).
- Prefer short sections; avoid marketing filler in engineering docs.

## ADR
- Add an ADR when a decision is durable and has trade-offs (backend/no-backend, caching strategy, hosting).
- ADRs go in `docs/adr/` and must include: Context, Decision, Consequences, Alternatives.
